Here's the optimized component:

```jsx
import React from 'react';

const List = React.memo(function List({ items }) {
  return items.map(item => <div key={item.id}>{item.name}</div>);
});

export default List;
```

After implementing this, you can test by verifying the component does not re-render when the items prop remains unchanged. If you have a large list, we can next explore virtualization options.
